<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESIDENT REAGAN'S FAREWELL ADDRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In his farewell address, President Reagan's closing comments concern the view 
from his White House window. He sees a "shining city on the hill . . . more 
prosperous, more secure and happier than it was eight years ago." 
</P>
<P>
In easy sight of the White House are people living in the park; Washington has 
achieved the "honor" of being No. 1 in violent deaths, due, no doubt, to the 
huge increase of drug use in that city. 
</P>
<P>
I'd like to have the name of the stuff they use to clean the White House 
windows. 
</P>
<P>
WILFRED COUZIN 
