<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION BOYS' BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
NORTH HOLLYWOOD MAULS MONROE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paced by forward Ed Davis' 27 points and a 38-point first quarter, North 
Hollywood High defeated Monroe, 110-74, in a Mid-Valley League game Friday 
night at North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
The Huskies led, 62-43, at halftime and outscored the Vikings (2-10, 1-4 in 
league play) in every quarter. North Hollywood (10-4, 5-0) won its fifth 
consecutive game and had 5 players in double figures, including Dana Jones, who 
scored 19 points, had 14 rebounds and blocked 5 shots. Harry Marks had 16 
points and 10 assists and Ray Fisher added 13 points for the Huskies. 
</P>
<P>
Ray Fisher scored 13 and Tommy Byrdsong added 11 for North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
Monroe's Derril White scored a game-high 32 points and Kenyon Wright added 16 
points for the Vikings. Mike Enriquez had 11 points for Monroe. 
</P>
<P>
MID-VALLEY LEAGUE 
</P>
<P>
Reseda 66, Van Nuys 42 -- Coley Kyman and Mike Basowski combined for 20 of the 
Regents' 30 first-half points as Reseda remained a game behind North Hollywood. 
Kyman finished with 19 points and 16 rebounds, and Basowski added 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
WEST VALLEY LEAGUE 
</P>
<P>
El Camino Real 60, San Fernando 59 -- Jason Steele provided the defense and 
Brent Lofton contributed the bulk of the offense as El Camino Real (5-7, 2-3) 
moved into first place. Steele blocked 6 shots, 5 in the first half, and 
finished with 9 points and 7 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
"Jason totally changed the way they went at us inside with his defense," El 
Camino Real assistant Jeff Davis said. 
</P>
<P>
Lofton, who scored 32 points on Wednesday, finished with a game-high 25 points 
on 12-of-18 shooting and added 12 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
San Fernando's Michael Wynn (9 points) made a 3-point basket with 1 second left 
to cut the deficit to 1 point. Ben Boyd led San Fernando (7-9, 1-4) with 15 
points. 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth 84, Canoga Park 52 -- Three Chatsworth players scored in double 
figures, thanks primarily to an overpowering inside game, and the Chancellors 
shot 60% from the field. Rick Garrick scored a game-high 24 points, and Sam Kim 
and Ramon Purvis added 18 and 16 points, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
EAST VALLEY LEAGUE 
</P>
<P>
Grant 63, Birmingham 51 -- Troy Mcleod had a season-high 19 points and 10 
rebounds to pace Grant (12-3, 4-1) at home. Grant's Nate Conner added 13 
points. 
</P>
<P>
Poly 66, Sylmar 65 -- John Bruner hit a 15-foot jump shot with 30 seconds left 
to give Poly (8-7, 3-2) the victory at home. Bruner scored a team-high 22 
points, Juan Estrada added 15 and Scott Copper scored 14. 
</P>
<P>
NORTHEAST LEAGUE 
</P>
<P>
Wilson 69, Sherman Oaks CES 49 -- Marcus Littlejohn scored a team-high 23 
points, but Sherman Oaks lost to first-place Wilson. 
</P>
