<HEADLINE>
<P>
APPLE POLISHER? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three cheers for Ken Adams' blasting of the L.A. Times' love affair with New 
York City (Saturday Letters, Jan. 14). 
</P>
<P>
But Mr. Adams is too general in his complaint. The chief culprit is Dan (Brooks 
Atkinson Is My Idol) Sullivan, who makes a yearly trek to Broadway to tell us 
all about shows that we might be able to see in two years, if a Los Angeles 
company is formed, that is. 
</P>
<P>
My favorite of Broadway Dan's New York reviews concerns Mike Nichols' recent 
production of "Waiting for Godot." Here was a show that sold out long before it 
opened; that was so packed that they had to hold a lottery to determine who 
could see it. It was a production that had nothing to do with L.A., but Dan 
spent half a page telling us about it. In the meantime, our Equity Waiver 
theater is relegated to one column in Stage Beat on Fridays. Jeesh! 
</P>
<P>
JON MULLICH 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
