<HEADLINE>
<P>
'PLAY IT AGAIN, SAM' PIANO MAY GO TO JAPAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Japanese coffee shop owner made a winning bid of 19-million yen ($152,000) 
for the piano played in the 1943 Humphrey Bogart movie "Casablanca," his son 
said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Shinji Ichimura, 48, placed his bid for last month's New York auction by 
Sotheby's through a department store in the western Japanese city of Osaka. 
Ichimura owns a coffee shop named Casablanca. 
</P>
</TEXT>
