<P>
COMMUTER PLANE LANDS IN CORNFIELD; NO ONE INJURED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUENA VISTA, Colo. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A commuter plane carrying 26 passengers lost power Friday and made an emergency 
landing in a cornfield, but no one was injured, authorities said. Airline 
officials had not determined what caused the engines of the United Express 
plane, a Convair 580 twin-engine propjet, to shut down. 
</P>
