employers to notify the state Department of Motor Vehicles whenever a school 
bus driver is discharged or suspended for causes relating to passenger safety. 
</P>
<P>
Bonds: AB 304 by Assemblywoman Doris Allen (R-Cypress) would authorize a 
$100-million bond issue to finance an anti-gang violence response program to be 
placed before the voters for approval on the June, 1990, ballot. 
</P>
<P>
Senate 
</P>
<P>
Floor Action: 
</P>
<P>
