<P>
WCAC ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SANTA CLARA GETS ROUTED BY ST. MARY'S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Something had to give Friday night at Santa Clara's Toso Pavilion when the St. 
Mary's Gaels played the Santa Clara Broncos. The Gaels were 5-0 in road games 
while the Broncos were 7-0 at home. 
</P>
<P>
Well, St. Mary's still is undefeated in away games after routing Santa Clara, 
76-48. The Gaels led from start to finish. An early 13-0 run gave them a 17-2 
lead with 11:52 to play in the first half. St. Mary's, which had lost 84 of the 
previous 118 meetings with Santa Clara, led at halftime, 43-25. 
</P>
<P>
Al Lewis scored 14 points and Erick Newman added 12 to lead St. Mary's, which 
remained in a 3-way tie for the West Coast Athletic Conference lead with 
Pepperdine and Loyola Marymount at 3-0. The Gaels are 15-1 overall. Santa Clara 
(11-5, 0-3) was led by by Jeffty Connelly with 18 points and Jens Gordon with 
17. 
</P>
<P>
USF 63, U. San Diego 58 -- Both teams were winless in the WCAC going into the 
game at San Francisco, but Kevin Mouton led the Dons to victory over the 
Toreros by scoring 20 points. 
</P>
<P>
San Francisco (9-7, 1-2) was playing without star center Mark McCathrion, whose 
father died earlier in the week. Joel DeBortoli added 14 points for the Dons. 
</P>
