<P>
GARDEN GROVE; 
</P>
<P>
ARSON FIRE DESTROYS 1 BUSINESS, DAMAGES 3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A gasoline-fed arson fire destroyed a Garden Grove travel agency and damaged 
three other businesses in a strip shopping center Friday morning, officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire began inside Travel World, 8907 Westminster Blvd., about 3 a.m. and 
spread to three other businesses through the attic, Garden Grove Fire 
Department Capt. Bill Dumas said. 
</P>
<P>
"Gasoline was used to accelerate the fire," Dumas said. "It was poured into the 
business and set afire." Investigators do not have any suspects, he said. 
</P>
<P>
It took 34 firefighters about an hour to contain the fire, which caused 
$400,000 in damage to the travel agency, an escrow company, a beauty college 
and a financial planning office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
