<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PREPS; 
</P>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
JALEWALIA SCORES 52 TO BREAK HER RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Amy Jalewalia scored 52 points, breaking her school record, to lead La Quinta 
High School to a 85-12 victory over Pacifica in a Garden Grove League girls' 
basketball game Friday at Pacifica. 
</P>
<P>
Jalewalia, a junior forward, scored 48 points against El Modena in December. 
She also had 12 rebounds Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Carrie Egan of Brea-Olinda set the Orange County single-game girls' record with 
56 points in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
Tanya Krill had 16 points and 7 rebounds and Heather Brannan had 8 points and 
10 rebounds for the Aztecs (14-3, 7-0). 
</P>
<P>
In the Sunrise League: 
</P>
<P>
Connelly 51, St. Mathias 42 -- Ranelle Kitajina scored 16 points to lead 
Connelly (5-1, 9-3) at St. Mathias. 
</P>
<P>
In the Century League boys' soccer: 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 1, Foothill 1 -- Steve Hope scored 8 minutes into the match for host 
Canyon (12-2-3, 2-0-2). Eric Fukuda scored 9 minutes into the second half for 
Foothill. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 3, Villa Park 0 -- Auviencio, Gustavo Santoyo and Gus Plasencia 
scored for Santa Ana (14-1-3, 4-0) at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
El Modena 2, Santa Ana Valley 1 -- Ronnie Murrietta and Marc Gonzales scored 
for host El Modena (5-5-2, 1-3). Manop Phinouwong scored for Santa Ana Valley. 
</P>
<P>
In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
La Habra 4, Buena Park 0 -- Ethan Saldana, David Karaba, Jose Mendoza and 
Eduardo Carabel scored to lead La Habra (7-5-2, 2-1-2) at Buena Park. 
</P>
<P>
In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 2, Rancho Alamitos 0 -- Diego Abbes scored twice to lead host Kennedy 
(6-4-3, 4-1-1). 
</P>
<P>
In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills 1, Trabuco Hills 1 -- Lars Slemming scored with 28 minutes 
remaining in the first half for Trabuco Hills (4-2-2). Brian Slayback tied the 
score for Laguna Hills (4-2-3) a minute into the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Orange 3, Costa Mesa 2 -- Omar Vasquez, Ed Gallagos and Eric McKay scored goals 
for Orange (6-8-3, 4-4-1) at Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge 3, Laguna Beach 0 -- John Szczuka scored 2 goals for host 
Woodbridge. 
</P>
<P>
In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
Santa Margarita 2, Capistrano Valley Christian 0 -- Oscar Mestre and Jason 
Forman scored for host Santa Margarita (8-6-1, 3-4). 
</P>
<P>
In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
Anaheim 1, Magnolia 1 -- Jesse Martinez scored midway through the first half 
for Anaheim at Magnolia. Mike Tsarnas scored midway through the second half for 
Magnolia (7-6-2, 1-1-1). 
</P>
<P>
Brea-Olinda 2, Valencia 1 -- Jason Ochs and Scott Maurer scored first-half 
goals for host Brea-Olinda (9-3-1, 3-0). Gary Thompson scored for Valencia 
(7-3-5, 1-2). 
</P>
<P>
In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor 2, University 0 -- Billy Castanha and Peter Scharnell scored 
goals for Newport Harbor (6-3-2, 2-1-1) at University. 
</P>
<P>
In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 1, San Clemente 0 -- Keith Rosenberg scored on a penalty kick 15 minutes 
into the first half for Irvine (6-2-7, 1-1-3). 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo 3, El Toro 0 -- Joe Max Moore, Andy Wortrich and Damon Hubbard 
scored for Mission Viejo (16-1-1, 4-0-1) at El Toro. 
</P>
<P>
In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
Fountain Valley 2, Huntington Beach 0 -- Todd Jackson and Kyle James scored for 
Fountain Valley (15-6-1, 3-2) at Huntington Beach. 
</P>
