<HEADLINE>
<P>
RODRIGUEZ REINSTATED, LEADS FULLERTON GYMNASTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton gymnast Eli Rodriguez was ruled eligible Friday, just 
before the Titans' season opener against San Jose State. 
</P>
<P>
With Rodriguez, the Titans pulled off a come-from-behind, 261-258.20 victory at 
Titan Gym. 
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez was suspended after his involvement in the stabbing of a former 
teammate in September. He was allowed to return to practice in November but 
whether he would be allowed to compete was unknown until Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The Titans trailed entering the final event, the high bar. Rodriguez (9.60), 
Diego Lopez (8.80) and Sven Lode (8.75) swept the event to give Fullerton the 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez also finished first in the rings (9.40) and won the all-round 
competition (55.55). 
</P>
<P>
In the women's competition, Fullerton's Stacey Harris won 2 of 4 events to lead 
the Titans to a 186.20-180.20 victory over Stanford. 
</P>
</TEXT>
